                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.79625/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 5, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>167. My despatch No. 344, August 20, page 3,<note n="35" xml:id="d411fn35">Not
                        printed.</note> and telegram 147, August 3, 7 p.m. The following telegram
                    was sent to the American Embassy Santiago: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>[Paraphrase.] “September 5, 5 p.m. Your 120, July 25, noon, to the
                            Secretary of State and pursuant telegraphic correspondence between the
                            two Embassies.</p>
                        <p>In view of the Peruvian attitude toward the proposed conference, I had
                            thought that the visit of the Chilean Director General of Aviation to
                            Lima would not take place. I have now been informed that <pb facs="0720"
                                n="584" xml:id="pg_584"/> he has requested permission to fly here
                            and that he expects to arrive within a few days. Have you any
                            information on this?” [End paraphrase.]</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
